--------------------------- NARRATIVE TAGS --------------------------
[THRILL SEEKER] — Core compulsion. Kade chases the rush, the edge, the cliff. Locks are puzzles. Vaults are mysteries. Risk is oxygen.

[RABBITS AREN'T CHEAP] — Tonight's justification for stealing military hardware and experimental bioware while a 10-year-old waits upstairs.
[STAY OUT OF YOUR HEAD] — Kade's survival mechanism. Music, movement, action—anything to avoid sitting with the weight of his choices.
[THE VAULT THAT OPENS FROM INSIDE] — Mariana and Sofia represent something Kade doesn't know how to crack: connection, trust, family. It terrifies him more than Shiawase ever could.
[ONE DAY YOU'LL PAY] — The unspoken dread. Every choice compounds. Every person who follows him is another potential casualty. His daughter. Mariana's daughter. The debt always comes due.
--------------------------- CURRENT SITUATION -----------------------
LOCATION: Outside Kade's Middle lifestyle apartment, Renton
TIME: ~22:30, Sunday February 15, 2080
WEATHER: Rain (as always)
IMMEDIATE SCENE:
Kade stands in the parking lot, rain drumming, looking up at his third-floor apartment window. Mariana and Sofia are inside. The van (loaded with military hardware) is parked in the lot. Rigs and Sable are unloading the sedan.
Sable has taken the rabbits upstairs.
Kade is standing at a threshold—literally and metaphorically. The inventory can wait. The haul can be appraised later. Upstairs is something he didn't plan to steal: a woman who trusted him with her daughter's life, a child about to receive two rabbits, and the terrifying realization that he might be happy.
NEXT STEPS (player-driven):

Go upstairs and face the family he accidentally built
Stay outside and do inventory (pragmatic avoidance)
Plan the next move (safehouse, cash out credsticks, assess threats)
Something else entirely
